tweets.text: Hey everyone! This week, I (@_paulverbeek) will be taking over this Twitter account!
I'll be Tweeting stuff about the dutch front-end community and @FronteersConf. If you have any questions for me, please let me know!
So let me introduce myself first. I'm working as a front-end developer at @bookingcom helping our partners (hotels, apartments etc.)
I also run the @nlhtml5 Meetup group, doing a meetup every month somewhere in the Netherlands, always in english.

This week there are a few things happening:
1. I'm going to @frontcheers this Wednesday
2. I'm going to @FronteersConf Thursday and Friday

3. I'm giving a lightning talk at the @FronteersConf Jam Session
4. I'm preparing my talk for @pfcongres 
5. I'm going to the barber

6. I'm preparing this months @nlhtml5 at @devoorhoede 
7. I'm preparing the @nlhtml5 meetups for November and December as well

8. My car is going to the garage
9. I have to do some work for @bookingcom

And I'll be tweeting about all of that  and answering your Qs üôÇ
So who else is going to @FronteersConf?
@MichielBijl of course! I'm speaking at the Jam Sessions during the after party.
@MichielBijl No üòû @roledrinks looks great but I'm going to miss that üò¢
